Maintain. Maybe you’ve been furloughed, or you’re being extra careful with money in these uncertain times. “Concentrate on doing a better job of maintaining the plants you have,” Yiesla said. Identify and learn about all your shrubs and trees; online experts such as the Plant Clinic can help. Learn about your plants as individual species, so you can understand what each one needs. If some plants have problems, figure out why. Cut back or divide overgrown perennials. Prune shrubs according to each species’ needs. Spread mulch around trees. Consider whether all your plants are in the right place in your yard, or if you should move or get rid of some.